-MwebzDdpO0lCGhiIYA6.text: Police are responding to a report of a person who may be in need of assistance.

-MwebzScDgjUwfhA3eup.text: Incident reported at Marion St & Wheelock Pkwy W.

-Mwejnkaz-G0NdQYg407.text: Police are on the scene and report a man armed with a gun has barricaded himself inside an apartment.

-MwejyGHSKrm1KA0dsuR.text: Police have directed nearby residents out into a hallway.

-Mwek1C3JkV16fh_0a6y.text: Police advise the man may be armed with a knife as well. He is making threats.

-Mwek69pQmgjTws8hBqL.text: Police have requested additional units to the scene.

-MwekC_KRHnLxC5Den2n.text: In an updated report, police advise he is armed with a knife.

-MwekH0Chj4eSl8HGVhK.text: Police have requested medics and fire crews.

-MwekJn477GzTRCF2qZ5.text: Police advise the man may be starting a fire inside of the apartment.

-MwekQYpVBT-rr2yKz9m.text: Police advise there is smoke coming out of the apartment.

-MwekvRI-MB6wf9SjXwA.text: Police report they have peered into the apartment through a window and they have spotted a fire.

-Mwel0oaNXFNnPGa70B8.text: Police advise the man is exiting the apartment and he appears to be unarmed.

-Mwel6GEGH63zw-gWG5a.text: Police report the fire has grown. They have asked fire crews to hurry to the scene.

-MwelEXXe5fGOCt9AHe5.text: Police are working to evacuate the upper floors of the apartment building.

-Mwelihvm1kSRCAKmMk5.text: Police advise they evacuated residents out of the first and second floors. One person is not accounted for.

-MwellgVZkd1XWW9lF8I.text: Police report they are working to evacuate the third floor.

-Mwelqrnu1sJK1LTB8m8.text: Police advise there are more residents that are being evacuated out of the first floor.

-MwelyWqPSxOsTNtEdXx.text: Firefighters report they are on the scene.

-Mwem1a3Td23hBwoxBta.text: Police are working to confirm that all officers have exited the building.

-MwemDtNy9BkgzURBnfS.text: Citizen user video from Rae_2cute shows the second and third floors of the apartment building engulfed in flames with fire crews below.

-MwemkZOrB2QNqL2hRJj.text: Police have requested units to ensure that residents do not reenter the building.

-MwemmOvHxUBUaiFWXan.text: Additional fire units have been requested.

-Mwemxg8yZAjZdnzvKu-.text: Police advise the suspect is in custody.

-Mwen3pFpfL1gLeNjWzu.text: Police advise they are working to evacuate more residents.

-MwenAhdxUpdxcYcf_K1.text: Police report they have requested two busses to the scene for the residents.

-MwenHUYeKwsTXQG-Tju.text: Police advise all of the officers have been accounted for.

-MwenSI9UGDludSqe4hW.text: Firefighters report they are working to extend a hose and begin a search of the building.

-MwenZsKQKS7eq8KZPtT.text: Citizen user carebear2020's video shows multiple fire units surrounding the building while plumes of white smoke rise into the sky.

-Mwenf25q-mO1xfzSTzr.text: Firefighters advise they are working to search and evacuate the third floor.

-Mwenh_-DWq0fhyGrFQh.text: Firefighters report they are attaching a hose to a hydrant.

-MwenqaqKHAzzVeliP8l.text: Police have requested additional units to help block traffic.

-MwenufV726X_dQyWCMN.text: Firefighters advise they are extending an additional hose to combat the flames from outside the building.

-MweoLwqV33iKOm6cR9e.text: Police have requested units to block off Marion St and W Hoyt Ave to prevent vehicles from driving over fire hoses.

-Mweop7ihn4RCTlcxmTo.text: Firefighters report the second floor has been searched. There is no one trapped or injured inside.

-Mwep3O2ZrY50JNN0xOj.text: Firefighters have issued a second alarm, requesting additional units to battle the blaze.

-MwepCwxr0AT45KnzOOL.text: Firefighters have requested an additional hose to the flames. They have extinguished some of the blaze.

-MwephDpxCf-A4AMSDzS.text: Firefighters advise they are working to confirm if all of the residents have evacuated the third floor.

-Mwepm3k-exyQ6zISq-2.text: Firefighters have requested fans to help ventilate the building.

-MwepqC0Dc5RDOaz_hkb.text: Firefighters report they have searched the third floor. There were no occupants.

-MwepyBAPk-7q_IGja_c.text: Firefighters advise they have not found any flames that have spread to the area above the apartment on fire.

-Mweq96lvxGNHPOB-Yif.text: Firefighters report they are working to evacuate the garden level.

-MweqL1KSoYLOCSHdtiX.text: Firefighters advise they found a dog on the third floor. They have safely placed the dog in one of the fire engines.

-MweqWRTouRjlkaIAbgk.text: Firefighters report metro busses are en route to the scene to provide temporary shelter from the cold and transportation for the residents.

-MweqardCmTvdkU4rYan.text: Firefighters advise they are working to extinguish remaining concentrations of flames.

-MweqskLOtlzQLeI8f2u.text: Firefighters report units are in the apartment on the third floor above the original fire apartment. There is smoke inside of the third-floor apartment.

-Mwer7q-AHDPJZbSxJRc.text: Firefighters advise the garden level of the scene has been evacuated. They are checking the roofline of the structure.

-MwesKk5fTl6Xxm_0I88.text: Firefighters report there are units on the roof and at the front of the apartment building.

nib.text:
An armed man who allegedly started a fire after barricading himself inside an apartment was arrested early Thursday morning in the North End, police said.

At 1:26 a.m., police responded to a report that a man was trespassing in an apartment near Marion Street and Wheelock Parkway West. 

The man left the apartment, but returned an hour later, according to a report from [KSTP](https://kstp.com/kstp-news/local-news/overnight-fire-damages-st-paul-apartment/). 

Police responded to the scene and escorted a woman out of the apartment safely. 

The man, who was armed with a knife, then barricaded himself inside a bedroom and made multiple verbal threats, including that he would burn down the building, police told local news reporters. 

As officers attempted to make contact with him, they observed smoke coming from the bedroom. 

Eventually, the man complied with officers' requests to exit the apartment and drop his knife. 

He was arrested for arson and the violation of a protection order, according to local news reports. 

Police evacuated the building as firefighters responded to the scene and began to put out the flames. 

Citizen user videos captured massive flames and plumes of smoke coming from multiple floors of the building. 

Residents were directed to heated Metro Transit buses, in addition to nearby apartments and other vehicles. 

The Red Cross also responded to the scene to assist displaced residents. 

Radio transmissions from the scene indicated two dogs were rescued from the building. Both were picked up by animal control as firefighters could not locate their owners.   

At 3:49 a.m., crews reported the fire had been extinguished. 

No injuries were reported.
